    "However, only a few of them are utilized in spatial modeling.",
    "In ML, model calibration refers to the alignment between predicted probabilities and the actual likelihood of events occurring.",
    "A well-calibrated model predicts probabilities that accurately reflect the actual probabilities of outcomes.",
    "Therefore, calibration is critical in probabilistic models, where the output includes probability estimates.",
    "Calibration ensures that these probabilities are reliable and can be interpreted as accurate confidence levels 152."
  ]
